snippet.textDisplay:
Are you Washed in The Blood?

1 Cor 15:1-4 KJV

Rom. 5:9 KJV

Rev. 5:9-14 KJV


And above all things have fervent charity among yourselves: for charity shall cover the multitude of sins.
1 Peter 4:8 | KJV

For the preaching of the cross is to them that perish foolishness; but unto us which are saved it is the power of God.
1 Corinthians 1:18 | KJV

I have chosen the way of truth:
thy judgments have I laid before me.
Psalm 119:30 | KJV

The wise in heart will receive commandments:
but a prating fool shall fall.
Proverbs 10:8 | KJV

For he hath made him to be sin for us, who knew no sin; that we might be made the righteousness of God in him.
2 Corinthians 5:21 | KJV

He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding:
but he that is hasty of spirit exalteth folly.
Proverbs 14:29 | KJV

And he was there with the Lord forty days and forty nights; he did neither eat bread, nor drink water. And he wrote upon the tables the words of the covenant, the ten commandments.
Exodus 34:28 | KJV

Heaviness in the heart of man maketh it stoop:
but a good word maketh it glad.
Proverbs 12:25 | KJV

Every man also to whom God hath given riches and wealth, and hath given him power to eat thereof, and to take his portion, and to rejoice in his labour; this is the gift of God.
Ecclesiastes 5:19 | KJV

Be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers: for what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness? and what communion hath light with darkness?
2 Corinthians 6:14 | KJV

We have sinned, and have committed iniquity, and have done wickedly, and have rebelled, even by departing from thy precepts and from thy judgments.
Daniel 9:5 | KJV

For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, much more, being reconciled, we shall be saved by his life.
Romans 5:10 | KJV

Whosoever denieth the Son, the same hath not the Father: he that acknowledgeth the Son hath the Father also.
1 John 2:23 | KJV

And they said, Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and thou shalt be saved, and thy house.
Acts 16:31 | KJV

But when Jesus heard that, he said unto them, They that be whole need not a physician, but they that are sick.
Matthew 9:12 | KJV

I am the door: by me if any man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.
John 10:9 | KJV

But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added unto you.
Matthew 6:33 | KJV


So shall the knowledge of wisdom be unto thy soul:
when thou hast found it, then there shall be a reward,
and thy expectation shall not be cut off.
Proverbs 24:14 | KJV

Likewise, I say unto you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner that repenteth.
Luke 15:10 | KJV

Will you repent?

But I have trusted in thy mercy;
my heart shall rejoice in thy salvation.
I will sing unto the Lord,
because he hath dealt bountifully with me.
Psalm 13:5-6 | KJV

Be ye not as your fathers, unto whom the former prophets have cried, saying, Thus saith the Lord of hosts; Turn ye now from your evil ways, and from your evil doings: but they did not hear, nor hearken unto me, saith the Lord.

Will you hearken unto God this day and forever?
